cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the analysis of a multi-layer complex network of human mobility using social media data and official migration data. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper may involve the development of software tools for data collection, processing, and analysis. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper aims to infer the structure of the global society through a community detection approach. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper may involve privacy and security concerns related to the collection and use of geo-localized data. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a less likely category but still possible as the paper may involve the development of algorithms for network analysis and community detection.
